Drifts into Bairstow on a flatter trajectory, pitches around leg-stump and goes straight on, Bairstow gets forward to flick and misses, is hit low on the pad and umpire Yeshwant Barde raises the finger in a flash. Even a review does not save Bairstow as it is clipping the leg-stump. What a tournament Chahal is having. Bairstow lbw b Chahal 56(40) [4s-8 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Ashwin to Dhawan, out Caught by Buttler!! A screamer from Buttler and RR have the breakthrough, A wicket in the very first over for Ashwin. In-drifter, Dhawan shimmies down the track to wristily lift it over mid-on. Didn't go too hard at it and relied on toming. Made decent contact and he'd have cleared most fielders.
